H0.text: points on a sphere or angles in a circle are measured in units called. Degrees

H1.text: points on a sphere or angles in a circle are measured in units called. Gradians

H2.text: points on a sphere or angles in a circle are measured in units called. Steradians

H3.text: points on a sphere or angles in a circle are measured in units called. radians

A4.text: The steradian (symbol: sr) or square radian is the unit of solid angle in the International System of Units (SI).

A5.text: A solid angle of one steradian subtends a cone aperture of approximately 1.144 radians or 65.54 degrees.
